avelength infrared interferometric observations of\ncircumstellar discs allow to study the inner disc regions in unprecedented\ndetail. The refined physical models can reproduce most of the investigated\nfeatures, including the photometric characteristics, the radial extent, and the\noverall shape of the visibility curves. Our multi-wavelength interferometric\nobservations combined with photometry show that the disc is similar to\nprotoplanetary discs with similar dust masses and efficient dust growth.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 Jan 2023 17:57:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 12 Jan 2023 14:44:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-01"}
