scaping ionizing photons, we\nfind that more than 80% of our galaxies have predicted $f_{esc}$ values larger\nthan 0.05, indicating that they would be considered leakers. The average\npredicted $f_{esc}$ value of our sample is 0.12, suggesting that similar\ngalaxies at $z\\geq 6$ have provided a substantial contribution to cosmic\nreionization.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 7 Jan 2023 09:32:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Feb 2023 14:47:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-04-26"}
